# New-card compat (wave 3): Giant Growth — scripted ACTIVE instant pump in combat.
#
# Giant Growth is a {G} instant: "Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn."
#   A:SP$ Pump | ValidTgts$ Creature | NumAtt$ +3 | NumDef$ +3
# (CR 601 casting a spell, CR 701 one-shot effects, continuous P/T modification
# until end of turn.)
#
# Tracking issue: Card Compatibility: Giant Growth.
#
# Aspects exercised:
#   1. Parses + castable as a {G} instant (spell cast assertion).
#   2. Creature-restricted targeting (ValidTgts$ Creature) resolves.
#   3. The +3/+3 pump is a COMBAT-RELEVANT continuous effect: a pumped 2/2
#      Grizzly Bears becomes 5/5, so it survives a 2/2 blocker AND kills it.
#
# Scenario (deterministic combat):
#   - P0: a Grizzly Bears already in play (no summoning sickness), Giant Growth
#     in hand, a Forest to pay {G}.
#   - P1: a Grizzly Bears that will block.
#   - Script: P0 attacks with its Bears; once blocks are declared, P0 casts
#     Giant Growth on its own attacker. The attacker (now 5/5) deals 5 to the
#     2/2 blocker (dies) and only takes 2 back (survives, 5 toughness).
#
# HOW TO RUN / VERIFY interactively:
#   mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/newcard_giant_growth_pump_combat.pzl \
#       --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs

[metadata]
Name:New Card - Giant Growth Pump Wins Combat
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts an attack with a 2/2 Grizzly Bears, then casts Giant Growth ({G} instant, +3/+3) on the attacker after P1 blocks with its own 2/2. The pumped 5/5 kills the blocker and survives. Backs Card Compatibility: Giant Growth (SP$ Pump, ValidTgts$ Creature; CR 601).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Giant Growth
p0battlefield=Grizzly Bears;Forest
p0library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Move to combat and attack with the Bears, then wait for the declare-blockers
# window and pump the attacker. PASS_UNTIL is timing-robust (CR 508/509).
PASS_UNTIL phase=declareAttackers
attack Grizzly Bears
PASS_UNTIL phase=declareBlockers
cast Giant Growth targeting Grizzly Bears

[p1_script]
# P1 blocks the lone attacker with its own Grizzly Bears.
Grizzly Bears blocks Grizzly Bears

[assertions]
# The pump spell was actually cast by the script (active-card aspect).
spell cast Giant Growth
# P1's blocking Grizzly Bears died to the pumped attacker (5 power vs 2 tough).
opponent graveyard contains Grizzly Bears
creature died Grizzly Bears
# P0's attacker SURVIVED (5 toughness vs the blocker's 2 power) — still in play.
me battlefield contains Grizzly Bears
